description.narrative: Strengthened participation of adolescents and communities in local development and child rights monitoring., which contributes to Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1: By 2020, all children in Malaysia benefit from strengthened national policies, quality social services and capacities that enhance well-being and enable them to survive, thrive and develop to their full potential.

description.narrative: UNICEF scaled-up digital engagement to empower young people to maximize their mental health and well-being; sexual reproductive health and rights, build trust in COVID-19 vaccines and SOPs, lead civic engagement initiatives and advocate for youth participation in decision-making both online and offline through the @KitaConnect,; Dewan Muda Malaysia, Chup! Jom Sembang Sek and VaksinNation programmes. A Ministry of Health partnership for evidence generation was established to inform policy and effective interventions for adolescent mental health. Generation Unlimited formed partnerships with UNDP, social enterprises and government to convene opportunities for young people on entrepreneurship, employability and social innovations. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
